The article summarizes remarks made by the President during a celebration of Greek Independence Day at the White House. The President expresses his delight at the event and welcomes members of his Cabinet and representatives. He acknowledges the presence of Archbishop Demetrios and thanks him for joining the celebration. The President highlights the significance of Greek independence and the support it received from other nations. He emphasizes the influence of Greek culture, art, and philosophy on the United States, particularly in the construction of government institutions and architecture. The President also recognizes the contributions of Americans of Greek descent to the country. He concludes by reaffirming the commitment to freedom, justice, and democracy.